n entity hierarchy. We’ll also explore how you can blend virtual content and the real world using anchors, bring particle effects into your apps, add video content, and create more immersive experiences with portals."}],"role":"sampleCode"},"coughski.jpeg":{"identifier":"coughski.jpeg","variants":[{"traits":["1x","light"],"url":"\/images\/coughski.jpeg"}],"alt":null,"type":"image"},"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes/coughski":{"type":"topic","abstract":[{"text":"No Bio on GitHub","type":"text"}],"url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/coughski","images":[{"identifier":"coughski.jpeg","type":"card"},{"identifier":"coughski.jpeg","type":"icon"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/coughski","title":"Kuba Szulaczkowski (3 notes)","kind":"article","role":"sampleCode"},"https://":{"title":"Blog","url":"https:\/\/","titleInlineContent":[{"text":"Blog","type":"text"}],"identifier":"https:\/\/","type":"link"},"https://developer.apple.com/wwdc23/10113":{"checksum":null,"url":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/wwdc23\/10113","identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/wwdc23\/10113","type":"download"},"https://x.com/coughski":{"title":"X\/Twitter","url":"https:\/\/x.com\/coughski","titleInlineContent":[{"text":"X\/Twitter","type":"text"}],"identifier":"https:\/\/x.com\/coughski","type":"link"},"WWDC23.jpeg":{"identifier":"WWDC23.jpeg","variants":[{"traits":["1x","light"],"url":"\/images\/WWDC23.jpeg"}],"alt":null,"type":"image"},"WWDC23-Icon.png":{"identifier":"WWDC23-Icon.png","variants":[{"traits":["1x","light"],"url":"\/images\/WWDC23-Icon.png"}],"alt":null,"type":"image"},"coughski":{"identifier":"coughski","variants":[{"traits":["1x","light"],"url":"\/images\/coughski.jpeg"}],"alt":"Profile image of Kuba Szulaczkowski","type":"image"},"WWDCNotes.png":{"identifier":"WWDCNotes.png","variants":[{"traits":["1x","light"],"url":"\/images\/WWDCNotes.png"}],"alt":null,"type":"image"},"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes/WWDC23-10111-Go-beyond-the-window-with-SwiftUI":{"type":"topic","kind":"article","url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc23-10111-go-beyond-the-window-with-swiftui","role":"sampleCode","title":"Go beyond the window with SwiftUI","identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC23-10111-Go-beyond-the-window-with-SwiftUI","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Get ready to launch into space — a new SwiftUI scene type that can help you make great immersive experiences for visionOS. We’ll show you how to create a new scene with ImmersiveSpace, place 3D content, and integrate RealityView. Explore how you can use the immersionStyle scene modifier to increase the level of immersion in an app and learn best practices for managing spaces, adding virtual hands with ARKit, adding support for SharePlay, and building an “out of this world” experience!"}]},"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes/WWDC23-10203-Develop-your-first-immersive-app":{"url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc23-10203-develop-your-first-immersive-app","role":"sampleCode","type":"topic","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Find out how you can build immersive apps for visionOS using Xcode and Reality Composer Pro. We’ll show you how to get started with a new visionOS project, use Xcode Previews for your SwiftUI development, and take advantage of RealityKit and RealityView to render 3D content."}],"title":"Develop your first immersive app","kind":"article","identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC23-10203-Develop-your-first-immersive-app"},"https://wwdcnotes.com/documentation/wwdcnotes/contributing":{"title":"Contributions are welcome!","url":"https:\/\/wwdcnotes.com\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/contributing","titleInlineContent":[{"text":"Contributions are welcome!","type":"text"}],"identifier":"https:\/\/wwdcnotes.com\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/contributing","type":"link"},"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes/WWDC23-10110-Elevate-your-windowed-app-for-spatial-computing":{"type":"topic","abstract":[{"text":"Discover how you can bring your multiplatform SwiftUI app to visionOS and the Shared Space. We’ll show you how to add the visionOS destination to an existing app and view your app in the Simulator. Explore how your SwiftUI code automatically adapts to support the unique context and presentation of the visionOS platform. Learn how you can update custom views, improve your app’s UI, and add features and controls specific to this platform.","type":"text"}],"url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc23-10110-elevate-your-windowed-app-for-spatial-computing","identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC23-10110-Elevate-your-windowed-app-for-spatial-computing","title":"Elevate your windowed app for spatial computing","kind":"article","role":"sampleCode"},"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes/WWDC23-10080-Build-spatial-experiences-with-RealityKit":{"role":"sampleCode","title":"Build spatial experiences with RealityKit","type":"topic","kind":"article","identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC23-10080-Build-spatial-experiences-with-RealityKit","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Discover how RealityKit can bring your apps into a new dimension. Get started with RealityKit entities, components, and systems, and learn how you can add 3D models and effects to your app on visionOS. We’ll also take you through the RealityView API and demonstrate how to add 3D objects to windows, volumes, and spaces to make your apps more immersive. And we’ll explore combining RealityKit with spatial input, animation, and spatial audio."}],"url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc23-10080-build-spatial-experiences-with-realitykit"},"https://github.com/coughski":{"title":"GitHub","url":"https:\/\/github.com\/coughski","titleInlineContent":[{"text":"GitHub","type":"text"}],"identifier":"https:\/\/github.com\/coughski","type":"link"},"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes":{"title":"WWDC Notes","url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes","images":[{"identifier":"WWDCNotes.png